name: Nothofagaceae
tag: The southern beech family. The leaves are toothed or entire, evergreen or deciduous. The fruit is a small, flattened or triangular nut, borne in cupules containing one to seven nuts.

name: Ticodendraceae
tag: The ticodendron family with only one species. A tree, 20–30 m tall, superficially resembling an alder in appearance, with alternate, simple leaves 5–12 cm long with a serrated margin. Generally dioecious, with separate male and female plants.

name: Casuarinaceae
tag: The she-oak family. Dicotyledonous flowering trees and shrubs, many of which have a distinctly pinelike aspect when seen from afar. They are naturally distributed in tropical eastern Africa, the Mascarene Islands, Southeast Asia, Malaysia, Australia, and Polynesia.
